  "title": "CNC engineer",
  "description": "<p>🚀 CNC Machine Tool Engineer (SG/PR)</p><p>Manufacturing Industry | Machine Tool Distributor</p><p>📍 Bukit Batok (Near Bukit Batok MRT, NS2)</p><p>🕒 Full-Time | 5-Day Work Week</p><p>🌟 Join Our Team!</p><p>We are a well-established machine tool distributor in the manufacturing industry, and we’re looking for an experienced CNC Machine Tool Engineer to join our growing team.</p><p>If you enjoy hands-on machining work, CNC programming, and maintaining high precision standards, this role is for you!</p><p>Job Responsibilities</p><p>As a CNC Machine Tool Engineer, you will be responsible for:</p><ul><li>Operating CNC milling machines and CNC lathes</li><li>Performing precision machining and part processing based on drawings/specifications</li><li>Conducting CNC setup and programming</li><li>Handling routine maintenance, troubleshooting, and machine upkeep</li><li>Ensuring quality control and compliance with safety procedures</li></ul><p>✅ Requirements</p><p>To be successful in this role, you should have:</p><p><br /></p><ul><li>Diploma or above</li><li>Minimum 2 years of CNC milling and/or CNC lathe operating experience</li><li>Strong knowledge in CNC machining, programming, and maintenance</li><li>Ability to work independently and also collaborate in a team environment</li></ul><p>💰 Salary</p><p><br />From $2,800/month (commensurate with experience)</p><p><br />🕘 Working Hours</p><ul><li>Monday – Friday: 8:30am – 6:00pm</li><li>5-day work week</li></ul><p>🏖 Leave Entitlement</p><ul><li>Annual Leave: 14 days</li><li>Sick Leave: 7 days</li><li>Monthly Leave: 8 days</li></ul><p>🎁 Benefits</p><p>Benefits and allowances will be shared and discussed during the interview.</p><p>🎥 Interview Method</p><ul><li>In-person / Video interview available<br /></li></ul><p>📩 Interested?</p><p>If you are passionate about CNC machining and ready to grow your career with a stable and supportive company, apply now!</p>",
